==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Thalline
<hw>Thal"line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a young
shoot or branch.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An artificial alkaloid
of the quinoline series, obtained as a white crystalline substance,
<chform>C10H13NO</chform>, whose salts are valuable as antipyretics; --
so called from the <xex>green</xex> color produced in its solution by
certain oxidizing agents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thallious</ent>⟦br⟧
